  "prompt": "What is the current bank rate?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, I don't have access to real-time data. Bank rates, such as central bank interest rates, can change frequently based on economic conditions and monetary policy decisions. To find the most current bank rate for your specific country or region, I recommend checking the official website of your country's central bank or reputable financial news sources. Here are a few central banks you might consider:\n\n- **United States:** [Federal Reserve](https://www.federalreserve.gov/)\n- **United Kingdom:** [Bank of England](https://www.bankofengland.co.uk/)\n- **European Union:** [European Central Bank](https://www.ecb.europa.eu/)\n- **Canada:** [Bank of Canada](https://www.bankofcanada.ca/)\n- **Australia:** [Reserve Bank of Australia](https://www.rba.gov.au/)\n\nIf you're referring to a specific commercial bank's lending or deposit rates, visiting the bank's official website or contacting them directly would provide the most accurate and up-to-date information.",
